The paper deals with game theory and machine learning algorithms applied to congestion games, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The use of no-regret algorithms and mirror descent algorithms also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses convergence and optimization, which are topics in both data structures (cs.DS) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
